Regression test for the `polymorphismResidual` guard (decision D3 in
the Stage-3 sketch): if a top-level term's type binds a universe
strictly above sort 0 after normalization, the Lean backend refuses
to translate.

Plain Type-0 polymorphism (Cryptol's `{a}` over types) is fine —
Lean handles those as ordinary `(a : Type) →` parameters. The
guard fires only when the term explicitly quantifies over a
higher universe, which would force Lean-side universe polymorphism
(the parked P4/P6 machinery).

This test passes a hand-built `(t : sort 1) → t → t` term and
checks the diagnostic.
